>
> > I just finished rebuilding a 2000 for my 75 bus. I installed the hydraulic
> lifters and am sure I will be quite happy with my decision. I have built
> type 1 engines and various American made engines, some using solid and some
> using hydraulic lifters. As long as either one is riding on the correct cam
> for your
> > application, you won't find any difference in how the engine runs. The
> only difference you will notice is you don't have to adjust them every 3000
> miles for the life of the engine! The adjustment is not difficult, but why
> spend the time when you don't have to if you go with the hydraulic lifters?
> I also recommend
> > going with a 2000 instead of the 1800. Same money, less miles on the case,
> and a little more power.
> >
> > "Thomas D. Adams" wrote:
> >
> > > I am currently deciding which engine configuration to get for my 73 bus.
> I have decided to use AVP as the rebuilder.
